visitor

Interface Visitable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ASTNode, MathNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActNode, AssignmentNode, ConstantNode, CubeNode, DifferenceNode, LvalNode, OutputNode, ProductNode, ProgramNode, QuotientNode, RValNode, SceneNode, SquareNode, SumNode

    public interface Visitable

    An interface used for using the visitor design pattern. It provides the accept method, needed while applying the visitor to every node.

    Author:
    Theodor Stoican

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void accept(Visitor v)
      A method that will be implemented inside every class that represents a Visitable object.

    • Method Detail

      • accept

        void accept(Visitor v)

        A method that will be implemented inside every class that represents a Visitable object. Used for calling the respective visit method.

        Parameters:
        Visitor - the visitor that will visit the node
